    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the iconic S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving powerplant utilizes eight individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio to deliver a linear power band up to its 8,400 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M-differential lock for optimal torque distribution. The chassis features Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and remains remarkably taut. Key preventative maintenance has been addressed, including rod bearing replacement and updated throttle actuators, ensuring the structural integrity of the rotating assembly. While the finish shows minor road-derived patina, the mechanical synchronization and performance metrics remain sharp, offering a pure analog experience for the discerning driver.",
